ean leader Kim Il Sung to win backing for the invasion of South Korea. The authors also examine the Sino-Soviet alliance, drawing on hitherto unknown secret protocols and understandings and the records of high-level planning that led to the invasion and to the Chinese intervention in Korea. The book is illustrated with 42 photographs and two maps and is the fourth volume in the series, Studies in International Security and Arms Control, sponsored by the Center for International Security and Arms Control at Stanford University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aLewis, John W., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aXue, Litai, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362211140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503622111423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503622111/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles